928
00:57:45,212 --> 00:57:48,548
- Elliot! Elliot Gould!
- What brings you here?
- Oh, hello.

929
00:57:48,674 --> 00:57:50,716
- Hello!
- I'm just, uh...

930
00:57:50,884 --> 00:57:52,468
How are you?
You look marvelous!

931
00:57:52,594 --> 00:57:55,138
- Is this another unexpected guest?
- I'm Opal from the BBC.

932
00:57:55,264 --> 00:57:57,181
Remember
the Cannes Film Festival?

933
00:57:57,307 --> 00:58:00,059
No, of course you wouldn't.
How silly of me.

934
00:58:00,185 --> 00:58:01,811
What are you doing...

935
00:58:01,937 --> 00:58:05,731
- What am I doing in Nashville?
- Excuse me. I'm sorry.

936
00:58:05,899 --> 00:58:09,777
- I'm doing this documentary...
- Excuse me, but Mr. Gould
does not give interviews.

937
00:58:09,903 --> 00:58:12,530
I don't know who you are
or what you're doing here...

938
00:58:12,656 --> 00:58:15,741
but I will not tolerate rudeness
in the presence of a star.

939
00:58:15,868 --> 00:58:17,535
Two stars.

940
00:58:17,661 --> 00:58:20,204
Just take her, Delbert.
Thank you very much. Good-bye.

941
00:58:20,330 --> 00:58:22,915
- Mr. Hamilton!
- It's gonna be all right.

942
00:58:23,041 --> 00:58:24,750
- No, listen...
- Who are you?

943
00:58:24,877 --> 00:58:27,545
Well, that's the price
of success, I guess.

944
00:58:27,671 --> 00:58:29,046
Certainly is.

945
00:58:32,759 --> 00:58:35,011
Go get a Goo Goo,
friends, and settle back...

946
00:58:35,137 --> 00:58:38,055
for 30 of the goodest
minutes in radio...

947
00:58:38,182 --> 00:58:40,016
the Goo Goo Grand Ole Opry!

948
00:58:40,142 --> 00:58:42,518
It's sent your way
by the makers of Goo Goo...

949
00:58:42,644 --> 00:58:44,937
the goodest candy bar
in the world...

950
00:58:45,063 --> 00:58:49,400
and King Leo pure stick candy,
the candy that roars with flavor.

951
00:58:49,526 --> 00:58:53,279
Now a big welcome, if you please,
for the Goo Goo man of the hour...

952
00:58:53,447 --> 00:58:55,406
Tommy Brown!

953
01:00:00,847 --> 01:00:02,515
Okay, this is it.

954
01:00:02,683 --> 01:00:04,433
- This is it, all right.
- Yeah, all right.

955
01:00:04,559 --> 01:00:06,644
- It's the new one!
- Yeah, I know.

956
01:00:06,770 --> 01:00:09,146
- It's the new one, all right.
- Have you got the time?

957
01:00:09,273 --> 01:00:10,606
Sure. Yeah. It's, uh...

958
01:00:35,215 --> 01:00:36,257
All right!

959
01:00:36,383 --> 01:00:40,136
I'm Del Reese, and I'm goin' back
to Haven Hamilton's group.

960
01:00:40,262 --> 01:00:43,014
- Remember me?
- This young lady's with me here.

961
01:00:43,140 --> 01:00:45,224
I'm being interviewed by her...

962
01:00:45,350 --> 01:00:47,351
and I really gotta go
to the bathroom.

963
01:01:03,368 --> 01:01:05,870
Oh, yeah! Thank you!

964
01:01:05,996 --> 01:01:09,415
Thank you, Tommy.
Beautiful job, as always.

965
01:01:09,541 --> 01:01:13,252
Say, Harold Weakly,
have you been on vacation yet?

966
01:01:13,420 --> 01:01:15,504
Gosh, no.
I've been busier than a puppy...

967
01:01:15,630 --> 01:01:17,798
in a room full of rubber balls.

968
01:01:17,924 --> 01:01:20,259
And if you're like me,
all that hustling and bustling...

969
01:01:20,385 --> 01:01:23,137
makes you want to sit down
and let the world go by...

970
01:01:23,263 --> 01:01:25,473
while you enjoy
a Goo Goo candy cluster.

971
01:01:25,599 --> 01:01:29,310
- Hey, Steve. She's with me.
- Excuse me. Can I help you?

972
01:01:29,436 --> 01:01:32,355
- I'm with these people here.
- Do you have a backstage pass?

973
01:01:32,481 --> 01:01:34,607
A pass?
They didn't need a pass.

974
01:01:34,733 --> 01:01:36,317
You need a pass
to go backstage.

975
01:01:56,088 --> 01:01:59,590
Go get a Goo Goo, the South's
favorite piece of candy for 62 years.

976
01:01:59,716 --> 01:02:01,634
- You ready to do the song?
- Right.
- Okay.

977
01:02:11,853 --> 01:02:14,688
I wouldn't worry
about killin' 'em. They're already dead.

978
01:02:14,815 --> 01:02:17,650
- Yes, thank you.
- You're lucky to be alive.

979
01:02:17,776 --> 01:02:19,944
Haven Hamilton!

980
01:02:20,070 --> 01:02:22,029
Yeah.

981
01:02:27,119 --> 01:02:29,620
Thank you. Thank you.

982
01:02:29,746 --> 01:02:31,831
Thank you.

983
01:02:36,670 --> 01:02:38,212
Excuse me.

984
01:02:39,339 --> 01:02:42,716
Well, I want to thank you
for that wonderful, warm welcome.

985
01:02:42,843 --> 01:02:46,011
And I'm sure
you meant to share it with...

986
01:02:46,138 --> 01:02:48,347
with Bud Hamilton,
my son, who's here.

987
01:02:48,515 --> 01:02:50,391
Stand up, Bud.

988
01:02:52,853 --> 01:02:55,521
Isn't he somethin' else?

989
01:02:55,647 --> 01:02:58,774
Yes, indeed. Yes, indeed.

990
01:02:58,900 --> 01:03:02,486
God bless you, and thank you
so much for that warm welcome.

991
01:03:03,655 --> 01:03:06,365
- How tall is that guy?
- Who?

992
01:03:06,491 --> 01:03:08,701
- Today I'd like to do
a special treat for you...
- Haven.

993
01:03:08,869 --> 01:03:11,579
- A brand-new song.
- Don't ever ask him that, John.

994
01:04:37,958 --> 01:04:41,877
That's funny, because...
Oh, there's Connie White!

995
01:04:42,003 --> 01:04:43,587
How are you, honey?

996
01:04:43,713 --> 01:04:46,298
You know what?
You remember you signed my album?

997
01:04:46,424 --> 01:04:49,635
Well, thank you
for coming to the show.

998
01:04:49,761 --> 01:04:53,180
I have a song I wrote.
I'll give you a call tomorrow.

999
01:04:53,306 --> 01:04:55,975
- That's fine.
- We'll just chat, you know, and...

1000
01:04:56,101 --> 01:04:58,769
You remember what I wrote on
the program? Will you remember?

1001
01:04:58,895 --> 01:05:02,648
- "I'm your friend. Connie White."
- I like your dress. I'm gonna get one too.

1002
01:05:02,816 --> 01:05:05,818
But I like the gold one
with the be...

1003
01:05:05,944 --> 01:05:09,113
you know, when you...
when you have no waist.

1004
01:06:13,637 --> 01:06:15,888
Thank you. Thank you.

1005
01:06:16,014 --> 01:06:20,309
- He's got the entire galaxy
on the back of his shirt.
- Thank you so much.

1006
01:06:20,435 --> 01:06:23,937
And now I'd like to do
a special old favorite...

1007
01:06:24,064 --> 01:06:26,231
the song that got me started
in this business...

1008
01:06:26,358 --> 01:06:28,233
that's been so kind to me...

1009
01:06:28,360 --> 01:06:30,277
a song you've loved
through the years...

1010
01:06:30,403 --> 01:06:32,529
and one I'm sure
you're gonna love tonight.

1011
01:06:37,160 --> 01:06:38,744
Thank you.

1012
01:07:16,366 --> 01:07:18,701
Well, now, Wilton's goin'!

1013
01:07:18,827 --> 01:07:21,286
Come on, Wilton!
Let's hear it for Wilton!

1014
01:07:35,260 --> 01:07:37,261
You gettin' ready, Joe?

1015
01:07:45,145 --> 01:07:47,980
Now everybody's goin'!

1016
01:08:26,436 --> 01:08:28,187
Yes, sir!

1017
01:08:30,899 --> 01:08:35,027
Well, thank you.
Thank you, and God love you.

1018
01:08:35,195 --> 01:08:37,196
Thank you so much.

1019
01:08:38,782 --> 01:08:40,699
Thank you.

1020
01:08:40,825 --> 01:08:44,077
Of course, we want to send
very special wishes...

1021
01:08:44,204 --> 01:08:46,163
and greetings
to our own Barbara Jean.

1022
01:08:46,289 --> 01:08:47,664
I know most of you read...

1023
01:08:47,791 --> 01:08:49,708
that she collapsed
out at the airport.

1024
01:08:49,876 --> 01:08:51,668
She's in the hospital.

1025
01:08:51,795 --> 01:08:54,046
She's in Vanderbilt Hospital
recuperating...

1026
01:08:54,172 --> 01:08:56,882
and Barnett tells me
she really cried real tears...

1027
01:08:57,050 --> 01:08:59,051
because she couldn't
be here with you tonight.

1028
01:08:59,177 --> 01:09:02,679
But I hope you'll send some letters
and best wishes and prayers to her.

1029
01:09:02,806 --> 01:09:06,767
That's Vanderbilt Hospital,
Nashville, Tennessee 27322.

1030
01:09:07,894 --> 01:09:10,729
And you tell her
Haven told you to write.

1031
01:09:10,855 --> 01:09:13,440
Now, as a special
stand-in for her...

1032
01:09:13,566 --> 01:09:15,442
we have her dear friend
Connie White...

1033
01:09:15,568 --> 01:09:17,861
who got out of the dentist's chair
this morning...

1034
01:09:17,987 --> 01:09:19,863
where she was having
some root-canal work...

1035
01:09:19,989 --> 01:09:22,574
and came all the way out here
to sing for you.

1036
01:09:22,742 --> 01:09:25,369
Miss Connie White, who's a friend
not only of Barbara Jean's...

1037
01:09:25,495 --> 01:09:27,037
but a friend
of yours and mine.

1038
01:09:27,163 --> 01:09:29,039
A wonderful singer
in her own way...

1039
01:09:29,165 --> 01:09:31,708
Miss Connie White!

1040
01:09:31,835 --> 01:09:34,711
Come on out, Connie!

1041
01:09:36,631 --> 01:09:39,716
- Hi, Del. How are you?
- I want you to meet John Triplette.

1042
01:09:39,843 --> 01:09:42,553
You look so good.
Wonderful!

1043
01:09:42,679 --> 01:09:45,138
Isn't she lovely, folks?
Isn't she beautiful?

1044
01:09:45,265 --> 01:09:47,266
We might want to talk.

1045
01:09:47,392 --> 01:09:49,560
- We'll talk about it later.
- Nice to see you.

1046
01:09:52,063 --> 01:09:54,189
Well, who do we have here?

1047
01:09:56,192 --> 01:09:58,443
- What is your name, honey?
- Paul Harris.

1048
01:09:58,570 --> 01:10:00,362
Paul Harris.

1049
01:10:00,488 --> 01:10:03,907
He's 13, he said.
And what's your name, honey?

1050
01:10:04,033 --> 01:10:07,244
Last time I saw a dress like that,
I was headin' for the junior prom.

1051
01:10:07,370 --> 01:10:09,162
You boys havin' a good time tonight?

1052
01:10:09,289 --> 01:10:11,415
The girl fell out of the car.

1053
01:10:11,541 --> 01:10:14,376
I want you to study real hard,
because just remember...

1054
01:10:14,502 --> 01:10:17,796
any one of you can grow up
to be the president.

1055
01:12:45,445 --> 01:12:47,237
Turn that off.

1056
01:12:47,363 --> 01:12:49,281
Okay.
One more minute, darlin'.

1057
01:12:49,449 --> 01:12:52,826
- Right now.
- She'll be through in a moment.

1058
01:12:52,952 --> 01:12:55,537
I want you
to turn it off right now!

1059
01:12:55,663 --> 01:12:57,330
It bothers me.

1060
01:12:57,457 --> 01:12:59,875
It bothers me too,
but I gotta listen, don't I?

1061
01:13:00,001 --> 01:13:02,169
- Why?
- Come on, now, honey.

1062
01:13:02,295 --> 01:13:05,630
I gotta go to the King of the Road
and thank her for you.

1063
01:13:05,798 --> 01:13:08,633
- Thank her?
- I gotta know what songs she sang.

1064
01:13:08,760 --> 01:13:11,970
You can ask anybody.
You can call.

1065
01:13:12,138 --> 01:13:14,973
You can send flowers.
You can send a message.

1066
01:13:15,099 --> 01:13:17,142
Come on.
Don't get upset, now.

1067
01:13:17,268 --> 01:13:20,145
You're makin' me ruin
my nail-polish job.

1068
01:13:23,066 --> 01:13:26,026
Do I tell you how to sing,
darlin'? Hmm?

1069
01:13:26,152 --> 01:13:28,779
Have I ever told you
how to sing a song?

1070
01:13:28,905 --> 01:13:32,657
That ain't the point.
I know why you're goin' over there.

1071
01:13:32,825 --> 01:13:36,453
Don't tell me how to run your life.
I've been doin' pretty good with it.

1072
01:13:36,579 --> 01:13:38,413
You go... Wh...

1073
01:13:38,539 --> 01:13:40,832
Let's calm down.
We're gettin' on each other's nerves.

1074
01:13:41,000 --> 01:13:44,961
You're goin' to the King of the Road
so you can hobnob with everybody.

1075
01:13:45,088 --> 01:13:47,714
- So I can do what? "Hobnob"?
- I ain't got no friends.

1076
01:13:47,840 --> 01:13:50,550
I gotta sit here
in this goddamn hospital.

1077
01:13:50,676 --> 01:13:54,513
- They're all gonna talk
about how I'm a nut.
- I ain't doin' no hobnobbin'.

1078
01:13:54,680 --> 01:13:56,598
Now, whoa, whoa, whoa.

1079
01:13:56,724 --> 01:13:59,476
"Barbara Jean had another collapse."

1080
01:14:00,520 --> 01:14:03,188
You know what?
While you're at it...

1081
01:14:03,314 --> 01:14:06,191
why don't you take her
some of my flowers?

1082
01:14:06,317 --> 01:14:08,985
- Are you through?
- No, I ain't through.

1083
01:14:09,112 --> 01:14:13,031
- Are you through, darlin'?
- Take her this nice black one.
That'll cheer her up.

1084
01:14:13,157 --> 01:14:15,534
- Why don't you try these?
- Are you through?

1085
01:14:16,828 --> 01:14:18,870
- And these.
- I said, are you through?

1086
01:14:18,996 --> 01:14:21,331
And why don't you try these?
And this...

1087
01:14:21,457 --> 01:14:24,042
Are you through, I said?
Are you through...

1088
01:14:25,461 --> 01:14:27,462
Are you goin' nutsy on me?

1089
01:14:27,588 --> 01:14:29,840
'Cause I won't stand for that,
Barbara Jean.

1090
01:14:29,966 --> 01:14:32,884
Huh? You havin' one of them
nervous breakdowns again?

1091
01:14:33,010 --> 01:14:34,886
- Huh?
- No.

1092
01:14:35,012 --> 01:14:38,014
You could've fooled me,
'cause it looks like you're ready for it.

1093
01:14:38,141 --> 01:14:41,226
You just settle down and shape up.
You understand?

1094
01:14:41,352 --> 01:14:44,312
The only reason I'm goin' over there
is 'cause I love you.

1095
01:14:44,438 --> 01:14:47,399
I don't love to go over there
and hobnob with them phonies.

1096
01:14:49,193 --> 01:14:51,570
Why do you make me
raise my voice to you?

1097
01:14:51,696 --> 01:14:53,905
Why do you put us both
through this?

1098
01:14:54,991 --> 01:14:56,366
Are you all right?

1099
01:15:00,329 --> 01:15:02,873
Come on, now.
Let's have a little smile for Barnett.

1100
01:15:02,999 --> 01:15:05,458
- I'm tired of this place.
- Come on, now.

1101
01:15:05,585 --> 01:15:07,294
Come on, now.
Get up.

1102
01:15:07,420 --> 01:15:10,505
You help me, I help you.
All right? Come on, now.

1103
01:15:10,631 --> 01:15:12,215
Come on.

1104
01:15:13,551 --> 01:15:16,011
Now, where's Barnett goin'?

1105
01:15:16,137 --> 01:15:19,264
Where am I goin'?
Hmm?

1106
01:15:19,390 --> 01:15:22,100
- King of the Road.
- And why am I goin' there?

1107
01:15:23,853 --> 01:15:26,938
- To see Connie.
- And why am I doin' that?

1108
01:15:27,106 --> 01:15:29,149
To thank her
for singin' at the Opry.

1109
01:15:29,275 --> 01:15:32,277
- Who am I doin' that for?
- You're doin' it for me.

1110
01:15:32,445 --> 01:15:34,029
That's right.

1111
01:15:37,992 --> 01:15:40,493
Now, I'm walkin' out now.

1112
01:15:40,620 --> 01:15:42,621
What do you say?
You say "bye-bye."

1113
01:15:42,747 --> 01:15:44,039
Bye.

1114
01:15:44,165 --> 01:15:45,624
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

1115
01:15:54,675 --> 01:15:59,095
Barnett?

1116
01:16:01,390 --> 01:16:03,308
- Hello, Ben.
- Hi.

1117
01:16:07,605 --> 01:16:11,483
Aren't they wonderful?
So marvelous.

1118
01:16:31,587 --> 01:16:33,838
What are you upset about?

1119
01:16:34,006 --> 01:16:36,716
She's really late.

1120
01:16:36,842 --> 01:16:40,804
- Well, she's not that late.
- No, she's late.

1121
01:16:40,930 --> 01:16:43,181
- Thank you.
- He's right over there.

1122
01:16:47,061 --> 01:16:49,187
I thought you were
very, very good tonight.

1123
01:16:49,313 --> 01:16:52,148
Thank you. Thank you so much.

1124
01:16:52,275 --> 01:16:54,609
She sounded beautiful.
She looked beautiful.

1125
01:16:54,735 --> 01:16:57,237
Well, Sue,
I didn't expect to see you.

1126
01:16:57,363 --> 01:17:00,115
- I wanted you to meet Julie Christie.
- Well, excuse my back.

1127
01:17:00,241 --> 01:17:02,951
- So nice to see you.
- Did you see Doctor Zhivago?

1128
01:17:03,077 --> 01:17:06,246
- She the one that got off the train?
- Will you be here a while?

1129
01:17:06,372 --> 01:17:08,290
- No, just passing through.
- Please sit down.

1130
01:17:08,416 --> 01:17:11,293
- Do sit down and have a drink with us.
- We're not staying.

1131
01:17:11,419 --> 01:17:13,253
You're English, aren't you?
I could tell.

1132
01:17:13,379 --> 01:17:15,338
Look at her.
Isn't she lovely?

1133
01:17:15,464 --> 01:17:17,924
- This is such a coincidence.
- I'm Del Reese.

1134
01:17:18,050 --> 01:17:20,719
Yes. I was talkin' about
the Christy Minstrels just this mornin'...

1135
01:17:20,886 --> 01:17:22,846
and now we have
Julie Christie here.

1136
01:17:22,972 --> 01:17:25,724
- I met you with Peter Finch.
- Oh, yeah?

1137
01:17:25,850 --> 01:17:28,059
- You won't sit down and stay?
- No, thank you.

1138
01:17:28,227 --> 01:17:31,813
- Julie has a friend at the Exit/In.
- I hope your stay is very nice...

1139
01:17:31,939 --> 01:17:34,733
and I hope you'll remember what film
facilities we have in Nashville.

1140
01:17:34,900 --> 01:17:36,818
- Oh, yeah, sure.
- Thank you. Good to see you.

1141
01:17:36,944 --> 01:17:39,571
- Have a lovely evening. Good-bye.
- Bye-bye.

1142
01:17:39,739 --> 01:17:42,032
Nice to see you.
Well, isn't that an honor?

1143
01:17:42,158 --> 01:17:45,410
- What a surprise. Julie Christie.
- Who's Julie Christie?

1144
01:17:45,536 --> 01:17:49,581
"Who's Julie Christie?"
She's a famous star.
She's won the Academy Award.

1145
01:17:49,707 --> 01:17:52,000
- Oh!
- No, I'm not kiddin'.

1146
01:17:52,126 --> 01:17:55,337
She got it for one of those pictures.
I don't know which one.

1147
01:17:55,463 --> 01:17:57,464
- She's done so many.
- Isn't he a gem?

1148
01:17:57,590 --> 01:18:00,884
- He's got the worst sense of humor.
- No, she's lovely.

1149
01:18:01,010 --> 01:18:02,969
Come on.
She can't even comb her hair.

1150
01:18:03,095 --> 01:18:06,264
Oh, you've got
a Hal Phillip Walker button.

1151
01:18:06,390 --> 01:18:09,184
No, it's Kennedy.
Isn't that rather ancient?

1152
01:18:11,562 --> 01:18:15,273
How strange! I thought everybody
in the South didn't go for Kennedy.

1153
01:18:16,984 --> 01:18:19,444
It's John Fitzgerald Kennedy.

